elements.title: Lowe Kong Meng
elements.contents: ... that Lowe Kong Meng (pictured) imported goods for Chinese miners during the Victorian gold rush and became one of the wealthiest men in the colony?

elements.title: Dr. Rick
elements.contents: ... that Progressive Corporation, an insurer, published 5,000 copies of a book credited to Dr. Rick, its fictional advertising campaign character?

elements.title: 92nd Infantry Regiment
elements.contents: ... that the flag of the French Army's 92nd Infantry Regiment was lost when the destroyer Siroco sank off Dunkirk in 1940?

elements.title: Shaylee Mansfield
elements.contents: ... that at age 12, Shaylee Mansfield became the first deaf actor to be credited alongside the voice actors for a signed performance in an animated production?

elements.title: the Holocaust in Bohemia and Moravia
elements.contents: ... that 250 Jews were imprisoned in a castle in Mladá Boleslav during the Holocaust in Bohemia and Moravia?

elements.title: Guy Thwaites
elements.contents: ... that Guy Thwaites and his colleagues hypothesized that the 1993 US hantavirus outbreak was similar to the mysterious medieval sweating sickness?

elements.title: HMS Swallow
elements.contents: ... that Pitcairn was named after the midshipman on HMS Swallow who first spotted the island?

elements.title: Hoosier Slide
elements.contents: ... that the Hoosier Slide was a popular tourist attraction until it was turned into glass?
